Pre-Game Insights: Bolivia and Venezuela will resume 2026 World Cup qualifying after competing at the Copa America in the summer.
Bolivia are in ninth place with three points, while Venezuela are in fourth position with nine points from six matches.
Bolivia experienced a disappointing campaign at the 2024 Copa America, leading to the sacking of Antonio Carlos Zago and the appointment of Oscar Villegas.
Venezuela made a knockout-round appearance at the Copa America but were defeated by Canada in a penalty shootout.
Venezuela are looking to qualify for their first-ever World Cup finals.
